# User-facing copy (in-game / tutorial)

When writing or editing **player-visible text** — tutorial dialogue (`tutorial_guide.json`, `gen_tutorial_guide.py`), Kanon bubble copy, toasts, overlays, i18n `tutorial.*` keys, card UI hints, etc.:

## Do

- Write as **in-world teaching**: explain what the player sees and what to do **now**.
- Match the tone of existing tutorial references in `i18n.js` (`intro_*`, `setup_*`, `t1_*`): clear, friendly, rule-focused.
- Use game terms consistently: **Main Phase**, **Live Phase**, **Performance**, **Success** pile, **Hearts**, **Energy**, **Stage**, **mulligan**.

## Do not

- Mention **prior versions**, redesigns, or “how it used to work”.
- Use **meta** framing: “real turn vs reading rules”, “for this lesson”, “advanced lessons later”, “we changed X”, “new feature”, “unlike before”.
- Break the fourth wall about the tutorial being a tutorial (except where the UI literally says Tutorial / Exit to Title).

## Examples

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| “You'll play a real turn, not just read rules!” | “I'll teach you the basics as we play.” |
| “Pick **You go first** for this lesson.” | “Tap **Go first** to play first.” |
| “We'll cover skills in advanced lessons!” | “Skills and baton pass come up naturally as you play.” |

Apply the same rules when mirroring copy to `tutorial_ja.json` or localized `tutorial.*` strings.

## i18n (required for all player-visible text)

Supported locales live in `i18n.js` (`LOCALES`, **en** + **ja** + **es** + **ko**). **Every new or changed player-facing string must ship in all locales in the same change** — not English-only.

### Korean (required — do not skip)

Korean (`STRINGS.ko` / `locales/ko.json` / `tutorial_ko.json`) is a **first-class locale**, same as Spanish and Japanese. **Every new or changed player-facing string must include Korean in the same change** — menus, missions, toasts, overlays, news posts, and JS-built UI. Do not ship English-only or en+ja+es without `ko`.

Source of truth for KO UI copy is `locales/ko.json` → inject via `python scripts/inject_i18n_ko.py` when using that workflow; otherwise keep `STRINGS.ko` in `i18n.js` in sync with `locales/ko.json`.

### Where strings go

| Surface | English source | Japanese / Spanish / Korean |
|---------|----------------|----------|
| Menus, screens, buttons, toasts, overlays | `i18n.js` → `STRINGS.en.*` | Matching `STRINGS.ja.*` / `STRINGS.es.*` / `STRINGS.ko.*` key |
| Static HTML labels | `data-i18n="dotted.key"` (+ `data-i18n-placeholder` / `data-i18n-title` / `data-i18n-aria-label` as needed) | Same key in `STRINGS.ja`, `STRINGS.es`, and `STRINGS.ko` |
| JS-built UI (lists, meta lines, dynamic buttons) | `t('dotted.key', { vars })` — no hardcoded English in `index.html` / `client/js/*` | Same |
| Interactive tutorial bubbles (`tutorial_guide.json` step `id`) | `dialogue` in JSON (English default) | **`tutorial_ja.json`** / **`tutorial_es.json`** / **`tutorial_ko.json`** entry keyed by step `id` |
| Legacy slideshow tutorial | `i18n.js` → `tutorial.*` | `tutorial.*` in `STRINGS.ja` / `STRINGS.es` / `STRINGS.ko` **and/or** `tutorial_ja.json` / `tutorial_es.json` / `tutorial_ko.json` |
| Title-screen news posts | `news.json` → `posts[].title` / `body` per post; optional `bannerStyle`: `crop` (default) or `full` | Same keys under `en` / `ja` / `es` / `ko` on each post |
| Server log lines shown in the client | `log_i18n.js` if applicable | Matching JA / ES / KO rules via `STRINGS.*.log` and `localizeLogMessage*` |

### Checklist before finishing a feature with text

1. Add **`STRINGS.en` + `STRINGS.ja` + `STRINGS.es` + `STRINGS.ko`** keys (or `tutorial_ja.json` / `tutorial_es.json` / `tutorial_ko.json` for interactive tutorial steps).
2. Wire HTML via **`data-i18n`** or JS via **`t()`** — avoid raw English in templates.
3. If UI is rebuilt on locale change, ensure **`refreshDynamicI18n()`** (or `onLocaleChange`) refreshes it.
4. Bump **`?v=`** on `i18n.js` / `tutorial_es.json` / `tutorial_ko.json` / `log_i18n.js` when those files change.
5. Run **`php scripts/validate_i18n.php`** after `STRINGS.es` or `STRINGS.ko` changes (checks both locales against `STRINGS.en`).
6. For **interactive tutorial** steps (`tutorial.json` → `tutorial_{locale}.json`):
   - Add curated dialogue under **`locales/{locale}.json` → `tutorial.*`** (or `TUTORIAL_EXACT_OVERRIDES` in `scripts/tutorial_i18n_glossary.py` for long prose).
   - Run **`python scripts/build_tutorial_locale_json.py --locale {locale}`** — glossary localizes game terms (**Member**, **Hearts**, **Performance**, skill brackets, etc.).
   - Run **`python scripts/validate_tutorial_i18n.py --locale {locale}`** — every step id must exist; ES/KO must have no English game-term leaks or mixed English prose.
   - **Do translate** game terms, tooltips, phase names, and skill keywords; **do not translate** character names, group names (Liella!, μ's), or Live/song titles.
   - Bump **`tutorial_{locale}.json?v=`** in `i18n.js` when that file changes.

### Korean specifics

- `cardLocaleName` resolves KO card/character names via `KO_NAME_MAP` (`i18n.js`, generated from `locales/ko_names.json` `characters` + `characters_jp` by `scripts/inject_i18n_ko_maps.py`) and song titles via `KO_SONG_MAP` (from `locales/ko_songs.json`). Character **and** song names stay untranslated in the underlying `cards.json` (`name_en`/`name`); only the display layer maps them to Korean.
- `cardLocaleType` maps JP `card_type` (メンバー/ライブ/エネルギー) to 멤버/Live/에너지 when no `card_type_ko` field is present.
- `cardLocaleText` looks for `card.text_ko` (populated for all cards with rules text; falls back to `card.text`); see `docs/locales/KO_PROGRESS.md`.
- Source of truth for KO UI copy is `locales/ko.json` → inject via `python scripts/inject_i18n_ko.py`.

### Do not

- Ship new menus, replay UI, error popups, or tutorial lines in English only.
- Add `data-i18n` without a Japanese, Spanish, **and Korean** string in `STRINGS.ja` / `STRINGS.es` / `STRINGS.ko`.
- Rely on English fallback for JA/ES/KO tutorial step ids — add `tutorial_ja.json` / `tutorial_es.json` / `tutorial_ko.json` keys for each new step `id`.

### Title-screen news posts (`news.json`)

- Explain **what changes for the player** — gameplay, deck building, ranked/casual rules, balance.
- Use **card names and point values**, not file paths, repo names, deploy steps, or dev jargon.
- Do **not** mention `news.json`, Hostinger, git, APIs, or implementation details.
- Ship **en + ja + es + ko** for every post title and body in the same change.
- **Card IDs** in post body (e.g. `PL!N-bp1-003-R＋`) are auto-linked in the news viewer — use exact catalog `card_no` values; idol names should match `cards.json` (`name` / `name_en`).
